    import android.text.TextUtils;

It is really helps a lot to check equality of Strings. &lt;br&gt; For example if you need to check Strings s1, s2 equality (which may be nulls) you may use **instead** of

    if( (s1 != null &amp;&amp; !s1.equals(s2)) || (s1 == null &amp;&amp; s2 != null) ) 
    { ... }

this **simple** method: 

    if( !TextUtils.equals(s1, s2) )
    { ... }
As for initial question - for replacement it&#39;s **easier** to use s1.[replace][1]().


